            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>remaining diced onion</strong>,<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> half </strong>the <strong>chopped ginger </strong>(save the rest for later!) to the pot and cook for 2-3 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>rinsed red lentils</strong>, <strong>remaining curry powder </strong>and <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>to the pot with 450ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[600ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[750ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 15-20 min or until the lentils are tender and starting to break down</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1674577954752-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1674577954752-x400.jpg",
