          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1674577954752-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the dal is cooking, grind the<strong> chopped herbs </strong>and <strong>remaining ginger</strong> in a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> until you're left with a smooth paste</p><p>Add your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>,<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> to the paste and mix to combine – this is your <strong>coriander chutney</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>tamarind paste </strong>with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> cold water</strong> – this is your <strong>tamarind sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
